  "prompt": "Why don't people answer me on Quora?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why people might not answer your questions on Quora:\n\n1. Low visibility of your question\n- Not enough details or context\n- Poorly worded or unclear question\n- Low number of followers\n- Asking about a niche or uncommon topic\n\n2. Competition from similar questions\n- Your question might have been asked before\n- Existing answers might already cover your topic\n\n3. Technical issues\n- Notification settings\n- Algorithm not promoting your question\n\n4. Timing\n- Asked during low-traffic periods\n- Topic not currently trending\n\n5. Quality of your profile\n- New or incomplete profile\n- Low reputation or credibility\n\n6. Complexity of the question\n- Too broad or too specific\n- Requires extensive expertise\n\n7. User engagement\n- Not enough followers\n- Limited interaction on the platform\n\nTo improve response rates:\n- Write clear, specific questions\n- Provide context\n- Use appropriate tags\n- Build your profile\n- Engage with other users' content\n- Ask during peak times\n\nRemember that response rates can vary depending on the topic and platform dynamics.",
